The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Odafe set to be best player
                                                   Odafe set to be best player
  - Dempo roar on last day; Churchill lose out on goal difference despite win; Bagan claim fourth spot
              OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT      I-League                                
	New Delhi: Churchill Brothers striker Odafe Okolie is set to be crowned the best player of the inaugural I-League.Though an official announcement is yet to be made, All India Football Federation (AIFF) sources indicated that the Nigerian, who scored 22 goals in the league, could be a runaway winner of the Best Player Award.         
	Besides this, Odafe will bag Rs 50,000 and the Golden Boot for being the top-scorer.         
	East Bengal goalkeeper Subrata Paul, who impressed everyone with his eye catching performance this season, is likely to get the Best Goalkeeper Award.         
	The only other custodian in the race is Karanjit Singh of JCT but most of the coaches in the I-League have voted for Paul.         
	The awards are given on the basis of appraisals made by the I-League coaches. Every coach is asked to submit three names for each of the five categories  best player, best goalkeeper, best defender, best midfielder and best striker. The coaches are also expected to mark their preferences.         
	Seasoned campaigner in Dempo rearguard Mahesh Gawli is once again a frontrunner for the Best Defender Award, though Gourmangi Singh of Churchill Brothers and Nirmal Chetri of Air India are also in the reckoning.         
	In the midfield, while Dempos Climax Lawrence is expected to be the best, Bhaichung Bhutia seems to have to no competitor in the striking zone. Dempo coach Armando Colaco will win the Best Coach Award for the SA Rahim Trophy.                                                                                                                         
